description:
When I was a young boy (1950's), I learned to play golf by closely watching the best players at the course I grew up on. I would then stand in front of a window and copy their swings... then I would go to the practice area to ingrain that look and new feeling to muscle memory. That WAS and STILL IS a great way to learn! It's called SELF-DISCOVERY! 

When you discover a helpful motion or thought ALL BY YOURSELF, YOU WILL NEVER FORGET IT! - I never have!  

At the age of 78, I'm still a mid single-digit player. My goal with this YouTube channel is to provide a platform for TEACHING and LEARNING! I will provide videos and detailed descriptions of the finest golfers in the world, their swings and some of their finest shots so YOU can learn and improve as I have. 

The focus here is geared toward TEACHING and LEARNING the short game (putting, chipping, pitching and wedge play from 120-yards in), but you will also see some of the finest, Tour-Proven full swings and descriptions as well.⛳️

description:
Road Trip Ventures is my journey through the second half of life. I spent my first career repairing cars, trucks and heavy equipment for over 30 years. Now I have more time to pursue new adventures. I've done some narrative film work, some corporate stuff, shot a few events and even some charity work as an intern. All of that can be found here if you look around. 
I enjoy bringing my experiences to the world. These days that means timelapse, and whenever possible, at night. I look for interesting places, and capture what it means to spend more time there than most people. In fact, I seek out places that most people won't visit; because most people won't visit them, yet might enjoy my visit. 
I'm always looking for something new to try out. If you like what you see, SUBSCRIBE. If your looking for a timelapse for your project lets work together. Your comments are encouraged. Without them you have no say in what you see here.
Thanks for stopping by, enjoy your visit.

Off-grid, VanLife, pojazdy elektryczne, gadżety, elektronarzędzia i inne 
Testuję, eksperymentuję, sprawdzam, pokazuję i objaśniam, choć się kompletnie na niczym nie znam.
Żaden z moich filmów nie jest poradnikiem, instrukcją czy zachętą do własnych działań i eksperymentów. 
Zrobiłem to co oglądacie, abyście wy nie musieli!
To czysta fikcja artystyczna, a ja jestem tylko wirtualnym bytem - nie istnieję, nie ma mnie, jestem wytworem chorej wyobraźni. 

UWAGA!
Nie nagrywam, filmów reklamowych ani opłaconych przez jakąkolwiek firmę "testów", prezentacji, pokazów itp. 
Jeśli chcesz pokazać swój sprzęt na moim kanale - dopuszczam wysłanie do mnie bezpłatnej próbki w celu przygotowania szczerej, subiektywnej recenzji. 
Nie dopuszczam możliwości jakiegokolwiek wpływu na moją ocenę przesłanego produktu. 
Widzowie mojego kanału będą wyraźnie poinformowani o każdym sprzęcie nie kupionym przeze mnie osobiście.

Come along for the journey. 

This channel will be dedicated to adventure, adventure photography and videography and the pursuit of finding true mental health.

description: We are Dave and Karen Beightol.  We live in one of the most historic areas of Colorado, at about 8500 feet in the rocky mountains. Central City, CO. to be exact. We have spent most of our lives as professional photographers, computer gurus, and web site designers. We came to Colorado from Indiana in 2000 to expand our photography skills and business. We found it a very tight, local market here at that time. We moved on into computer and web services, where we made a good living for many years. We now own and operate the only all natural restaurant on the mountain. Burger Joint. Nothing from a box, can or microwave, is our motto. After semi retiring into the natural food business, we have decided to get back to our love of images. With our computer and technical background, combined with our photo and video skills, we though that areal imaging via UAV drones would be a perfect fit. Add this to a geographically spectacular location and here we are. NOW FCC LICENSED!
